First Lady Michelle Obama will be participating in two upcoming events. On Wednesday, December 9th, she will visit Joint Base Anacostia-Bolling as part of the Joining Forces initiative. She will give brief remarks and deliver toys and gifts donated by Executive Office of the President staff to the Marine Corps Reserve Toys for Tots Campaign. On Monday, December 14th, Mrs. Obama will continue the tradition started by Bess Truman by visiting the Children's National Health System in Washington, DC. She will take a tour, visit patients, and thank the Children's staff for their work. After the tour, she will read to children and answer their questions in the hospital's atrium.